15 "SECTION 2.
16 (a) The Gwinnett County Board of Education is authorized to fix the salary and
17 compensation of the members of the Gwinnett County Board of Education subject to the
18 following conditions:
19 (1) Any increase in salary or compensation for members of the Gwinnett County Board
20 of Education shall not be effective until the first day of January of the year following the
21 next general election held after the date on which the action to increase the compensation
22 was taken;
23 (2) The Gwinnett County Board of Education shall take no action to increase the salary
24 or compensation of the members of the board until notice of intent to take such action and
25 the fiscal impact of such action has been published in a newspaper designated as the legal
26 organ for the county at least once a week for three consecutive weeks immediately
27 preceding the meeting at which the action is taken; and
28 (3) Such action shall not be taken during the period of time beginning with the date that
29 candidates for election as members of the Gwinnett County Board of Education may first
30 qualify as such candidates and ending with the first day of January following the date of
31 qualification.
32 This subsection shall not affect the power of the General Assembly at any time to increase
33 or decrease any or all of such compensation or to withdraw the authority otherwise granted
34 under this subsection.
35 (b)(1) The provisions of subsection (a) of this section shall be suspended in the event:
36 (A) That the Gwinnett County Board of Education approves a contract termination
37 payout to the superintendent so as to terminate such contract prior to the contractual end
38 date of such contract; or
39 (B) Such contractual payout payments are still being made to one or more former
40 superintendents.
