41 (2) The suspension provided for in paragraph (1) of this subsection shall remain in force
42 until such time as either:
43 (A) The compensation that would have otherwise been paid to the members of the
44 board pursuant to subsection (a) of this section equals the amount:
45 (i) Paid to a superintendent to terminate such superintendent's contract prior to the
46 contractual end date of such contract; or
47 (ii) Still being paid to any former superintendents as a result of the early termination
48 of one or more contracts that are being made on the effective date of this subsection;
49 or
50 (B) All members of the Gwinnett County Board of Education who were in office when
51 the board approved a contract termination payout to a superintendent prior to the
52 contractual end date of such contract have ceased serving on such board.
53 (3) In the event that the compensation of the board members is suspended by operation
54 of this subsection, the members of the board of education shall receive the per diem
55 provided for by O.C.G.A. Code Section 20-2-55.
56 SECTION 2A.
57 The Gwinnett County Board of Education and the Gwinnett County Public Schools shall
58 not infringe upon right of individual board members to communicate with constituents, the
59 general public, or members of the media; provided, however, that nothing in this section
60 shall prevent such board from adopting policies to ensure that:
61 (1) Confidential discussions occurring during an executive session pursuant to Chapter
62 14 of Title 50 of the O.C.G.A., or
63 (2) Any information that is deemed confidential, privileged, private, or exempt from
64 disclosure under federal or state law
65 is not disclosed or disseminated in an unauthorized manner."
